# characters of Shahnameh
rostam :: legendary hero :: The greatest warrior of Iran; symbol of strength, loyalty, and invincibility.
sohrab :: tragic hero :: Son of Rostam; a powerful young warrior whose fate defines epic tragedy.
zal :: noble hero :: Father of Rostam; born with white hair and raised by the mythical Simurgh.
simurgh :: mythical guardian :: A wise, benevolent bird; symbol of knowledge, healing, and destiny.
kaykavus :: king :: Proud and reckless king of Iran; driven by ambition and poor judgment.
kaykhosrow :: just king :: Righteous and wise ruler; symbol of justice, balance, and divine favor.
jamshid :: mythical king :: Legendary ruler of prosperity and civilization, later ruined by hubris.
zahhak :: tyrant king :: Cruel ruler corrupted by evil; embodiment of oppression and decay.
fereydun :: liberator king :: Hero-king who overthrew Zahhak; symbol of justice and renewal.
esfandiyar :: invincible hero :: Holy warrior with an invulnerable body; bound by duty and tragedy.
gordafarid :: warrior woman :: Brave female warrior who fought Sohrab; symbol of courage and honor.
tahmineh :: noble woman :: Princess of Samangan; mother of Sohrab, known for strength and resolve.
manuchehr :: king :: Ruler driven by lineage and revenge; represents royal continuity.
afrasiab :: enemy king :: King of Turan; Iran’s greatest adversary, cunning and ruthless.
giv :: hero :: Loyal Iranian warrior known for endurance and long journeys.
gudarz :: elder hero :: Wise and experienced commander; symbol of loyalty and leadership.
bijan :: young hero :: Brave warrior central to a famous love and rescue story.
manijeh :: princess :: Daughter of Afrasiab; symbol of loyalty, love, and sacrifice.
tus :: general :: Proud Iranian commander; capable but impulsive.
fariborz :: prince :: Son of Kay Kavus; ambitious yet often overshadowed.
arash :: archer hero :: Legendary archer who sacrificed his life to define Iran’s borders.
keyumars :: first king :: The first human and king; symbol of beginnings and order.
hushang :: king :: Discoverer of fire; emblem of knowledge and progress.
tahmuras :: king :: Civilizing ruler who subdued demons and promoted learning.
garshasp :: ancient hero :: Mighty warrior from early generations; known for raw strength.
nariman :: hero :: Grandfather of Rostam; symbol of heroic lineage.
sam :: hero :: Father of Zal; respected and powerful warrior.
farhad :: lover hero :: Tragic figure of devotion, endurance, and impossible love.

# characters of Khosrow & Shirin
khosrow :: king :: Sassanian ruler whose love and power shape a legendary romance.
shirin :: queen :: Independent and intelligent woman; symbol of love, dignity, and strength.
farhad :: tragic lover :: Devoted sculptor whose love becomes a symbol of sacrifice.
shapur :: court artist :: Loyal advisor and messenger who shapes the lovers’ fate.

# characters of 1001 Shab
sinbad :: sailor :: Legendary seafarer known for perilous voyages and resilience.
aladdin :: adventurer :: Clever young man whose life changes through magic and wit.
jafar :: vizier :: Ambitious royal advisor; symbol of intrigue and power hunger.
alibaba :: woodcutter :: Poor man who discovers a secret treasure cave.
morgiana :: servant :: Brave and clever woman who repeatedly saves Ali Baba.
solomon :: king :: Wise ruler with authority over humans, animals, and jinn.
harunalrashid :: caliph :: Just ruler who wandered among his people in disguise.
jaafarbaramaki :: vizier :: Trusted minister known for intelligence and loyalty.
nuraddin :: nobleman :: Romantic hero caught between love and fate.
anisaljalis :: court lady :: Gifted woman central to political intrigue.
hasanbasri :: merchant :: Adventurous figure drawn into supernatural realms.
qamaralzaman :: prince :: Romantic hero whose love defies distance and destiny.

# Iran cities
tehran :: tehran :: Capital of Iran; political, economic, and technological center.
isfahan :: isfahan :: Former imperial capital; symbol of Persian art and architecture.
shiraz :: fars :: City of poets and gardens; heart of Persian literature.
mashhad :: razavikhorasan :: Major religious city; home of Imam Reza shrine.
tabriz :: eastazerbaijan :: Historic trade hub and center of Azeri culture.
yazd :: yazd :: Ancient desert city; known for windcatchers and Zoroastrian heritage.
kerman :: kerman :: Historic southeastern city; gateway to desert trade routes.
ahvaz :: khuzestan :: Industrial river city; center of oil production.
qom :: qom :: Religious and scholarly center of Shi’a studies.
hamedan :: hamedan :: One of the world’s oldest cities; ancient Ecbatana.
kermanshah :: kermanshah :: Western cultural city with rich Kurdish heritage.
rasht :: gilan :: Caspian city known for trade, cuisine, and rain.
sari :: mazandaran :: Green coastal capital with deep historical roots.
bandarabbas :: hormozgan :: Strategic southern port on the Persian Gulf.
zanjan :: zanjan :: Northwestern city known for craftsmanship.
sanandaj :: kurdistan :: Cultural capital of Iranian Kurdistan.
ardabil :: ardabil :: Birthplace of the Safavid dynasty.
qazvin :: qazvin :: Former capital and administrative center.
bushehr :: bushehr :: Ancient port city with maritime heritage.
birjand :: southkhorasan :: Eastern frontier city with desert architecture.

# Iranian icons
hafez :: poet :: Master of Persian lyric poetry; symbol of wisdom and mysticism.
saadi :: poet :: Classical poet known for moral insight and humanism.
ferdowsi :: poet :: Author of Shahnameh; preserver of Persian identity.
rumi :: mystic poet :: Philosopher of love and spiritual unity.
attar :: poet :: Mystic poet; author of “The Conference of the Birds.”
khayyam :: polymath :: Poet, mathematician, and astronomer.
nezami :: poet :: Master storyteller of Persian romantic epics.
bidel :: poet :: Philosopher-poet of deep mystical imagery.
avicennan :: physician philosopher :: Influential thinker of the Islamic Golden Age.
razi :: physician chemist :: Pioneer of experimental medicine.
farabi :: philosopher :: Architect of Islamic political philosophy.
biruni :: scientist :: Polymath of astronomy, geography, and culture.
kharazmi :: mathematician :: Father of algebra.
kamalolmolk :: painter :: Master of realism in Persian art.
sohrabsepehri :: poet painter :: Modern artist blending nature and mysticism.
shajarian :: vocalist :: Iconic master of Persian classical singing.
nazerian :: musician :: Renowned performer of Persian and Kurdish music.
forough :: poet :: Influential modern poet of honesty and rebellion.
siminbehbahani :: poet :: Voice of modern Persian poetry and freedom.
anahita :: mythic figure :: Ancient symbol of water, life, and purity.
mehr :: ancient concept :: Symbol of light, covenant, and friendship.
tir :: ancient concept :: Associated with rain and renewal.

# iconic Iranian women
foroughfarrokhzad :: poet :: Groundbreaking modern poet who reshaped Persian literature.
siminbehbahani :: poet :: “Lioness of Iran”; voice of freedom and social justice.
parvinetesami :: poet :: Master of moral and philosophical poetry.
shirinebadi :: lawyer :: Nobel laureate and global human rights advocate.
farrokhlaqa :: artist :: Visionary contemporary artist of modern abstraction.
leilahatami :: actress :: Internationally acclaimed actress of subtle depth.
golshifteh :: actress musician :: Symbol of artistic freedom beyond borders.
gordafarid :: mythic warrior :: Legendary woman warrior; symbol of resistance.
mitra :: ancient deity :: Symbol of covenant, justice, and light.
farmanfarmayan :: patron :: Influential figure in cultural and social reform.
